# Only item_icons/ is ignored -- it's regenerated by tools/fetch_item_icons.py
# (run it after cloning), so committing it would just be redundant. Assets/ui/,
# Assets/map/, and Assets/maps/ are NOT ignored on purpose: those are your
# manually-captured screenshots/crops with no script to regenerate them, and
# the macro's image-search navigation (nav_start, victory, stage rows, map
# cards, ...) flatly doesn't work without them -- excluding them would ship
# a broken macro to anyone who clones the repo.
Assets/item_icons/
# Same reasoning -- regenerated by tools/fetch_stage_data.py.
Assets/stage_data.json

# Generated at runtime -- debug captures, recorded paths, saved templates,
# the task queue. None of it is meaningful to anyone but you.
debug/
Paths/
Templates/

# Personal config -- includes your Discord webhook URL, hotkeys, calibrated
# regions, etc. Never commit this.
settings.json

# Runtime log -- local troubleshooting only, no reason to version it.
*.log

# Python
__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/
venv/

# Build/dist output, if this ever gets packaged
build/
dist/
*.spec
